Coding Standards (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
These standards MUST be followed in EVERY code change.

1. File Headers with Author
EVERY Kotlin file must have an author header:

kotlin
// Author: [LLM Name] - [Brief description of changes/additions]
// Example: Author: DeepSeek - Fixed widget toggle persistence
// Example: Author: Claude - Added geocoding fallback logic
CORRECT:

kotlin
// Author: Claude - Initial implementation of SettingsActivity

package com.augusteenterprise.giglens.ui

import android.os.Bundle
// ...
WRONG:

kotlin
// No author header

package com.augusteenterprise.giglens.ui
2. No Hardcoded Values
All configuration values must be stored in database or asset files.

CORRECT:

kotlin
// Using AppConfigKeys constant
GlobalScope.launch {
    appDao.setValue(AppConfigKeys.WIDGET_ENABLED, "true")
}

// Using ScorerConfigKeys constant
val costPerMile = scorerDao.getValue(ScorerConfigKeys.COST_PER_MILE) ?: 0.90
WRONG:

kotlin
// Hardcoded string key
GlobalScope.launch {
    appDao.setValue("widget_enabled", "true")  // NO!
}

// Hardcoded value
val costPerMile = 0.90  // NO! Should come from config
3. Exception Handling - NO SILENT CATCH
All exceptions must be explicitly logged.

CORRECT:

kotlin
try {
    riskyOperation()
} catch (e: Exception) {
    Log.e(TAG, "Operation failed: ${e.message}", e)
    // Handle or rethrow
}
WRONG:

kotlin
try {
    riskyOperation()
} catch (e: Exception) {
    // Empty catch - SILENT FAILURE - NO!
}
4. Subprocess Calls - No stdout=PIPE
When using ProcessBuilder, write output to log files, not stdout.

CORRECT:

kotlin
val process = ProcessBuilder("command")
    .redirectErrorStream(true)
    .start()
process.waitFor()
WRONG:

kotlin
val process = ProcessBuilder("command")
    .redirectOutput(ProcessBuilder.Redirect.PIPE)  // NO!
    .start()
5. CHANGELOG.md Updates
Every code change must update CHANGELOG.md in the SAME commit.

